'''Florence Tsague Assopgoum'''&nbsp;(born in 1977 in Bafou-Djuttitsa, west of Cameroon in West Africa), is a Cameroonian political scientist and writer.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.gh/books?id=2arrKG21qEYC&dq=Florence+Tsague+Assopgoum&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_tbjo767XAhVoIcAKHfUZAbUQ6AEIJDAA |title=Ethnizität und ethnische Konflikte in Afrika |last=Assopgoum |first=Florence Tsague|publisher=GRIN Verlag |isbn=9783640261949 |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.gh/books?id=Pfi8p9W6i28C&dq=Florence+Tsague+Assopgoum&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=Migration aus Afrika in die EU: Eine Analyse der Berichterstattung in deutschen und senegalesischen Zeitungen|last=Assopgoum|first=Florence Tsagué|date=October 26, 2011|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|year=|isbn=9783531183732|location=|pages=|language=de}}</ref>
== Career == Tsagué A. is a member of several organizations such as the [[African Union]] in [[Siegerland]] (region of Germany) and African Development Initiative. She is an accredited lecturer at Europäische Akademie NRW. In addition to her publications in the press such as Africa Positive, She organizes reading sessions in the Siegen area. In 2008 she took part in Siegen Wittgenstein's poets and writers tour entitled "Menschen zwischen den Kulturen". She writes news, poems and novels. Her first novel, Famous Women, Unknown Co-Wives, was published in August 2009. In this novel, which takes the reader into a rich world of cultures and traditions, she talks about the discrimination of women and girls in the inheritance system in Cameroon. It also contains themes on [[polygamy]], child abuse and complicit silence.The book pleads for the adaptation of the culture that addresses the urgent problems of its time and thus participates in a debate which in African societies are dominated by the elders. This novel was nominated for the Pan-literate prize of the association "Africa Culture Rhein-Neckar".<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afrika-kulturinstitut.de/index.php/kuturprojekte-2010/62-philomene-atyame|title=Die Nomminees für PANLITERATE|last=|first=|date=|year=2010|publisher=Africa Culture Rhein-Neckar e.V.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110308154937/http://www.afrika-kulturinstitut.de/index.php/kuturprojekte-2010/62-philomene-atyame |archive-date=2011-03-08|dead-url=yes|access-date=November 8, 2017}}</ref>
