{{Infobox language |name=Ku |altname=[[Bo people (China)|Bo]] |states=[[China]] |ethnicity=[[Yi people|Yi]] |speakers= |date= |ref=<ref name="Hsiu2013">Hsiu, Andrew. 2013. ''[https://zenodo.org/record/1127796 New endangered Tibeto-Burman languages of southwestern China: Mondzish, Longjia, Pherbu, and others]''. Presented at ICSTLL 46, Dartmouth College. {{doi|10.5281/zenodo.1127796}} </ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Nisoish languages|Nisoish]] |fam6=[[Northern Loloish languages|Northern Loloish]] |fam7=[[Nasu language|Nasoid]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Ku''' ([[wikt:Autonym|autonym]]: ''ku˥'') is a [[Loloish languages|Loloish]] [[language cluster]] of southeastern [[Yunnan]], China.
==Varieties== There are three different varieties of Ku.<ref name="msealangs">{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/site/msealangs/home|website=sites.google.com|title=MSEA Languages|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Speakers of each consider themselves to be separate ethnic groups.<ref name="Hsiu2013"/> However, they are officially classified by the Chinese government as ethnic [[Yi people|Yi]].<ref>Qiubei County Gazetteer 丘北县志 (1999)</ref>
*Ku (autonym: ''ku˥'') is spoken in Bainitang 白泥塘,<ref name="ynszxc">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=198759|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=丘北县舍得彝族乡矣白村民委白泥塘村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Shede Township 舍得彝族乡, [[Qiubei County]], [[Yunnan]] Province. They are also locally known as the [[Bo people (China)|Bo]] ({{zh|c={{linktext|僰|人}}|p={{linktext|Bó| rén}}}}), and continue to build [[hanging coffins]]. The Ku of Bainitang claim that their ancestors had migrated from [[Yibin]], Sichuan.<ref>Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. ''[https://sites.google.com/site/msealangs/sino-tibetan/ku-bainitang Ku (Bainitang) audio word list]''. Zenodo. {{doi|10.5281/zenodo.1122951}}</ref> *Another variety of Ku (autonym: ''ku˥'') in Wujiazhai 五家寨,<ref name="ynszxc2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=198738|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=丘北县舍得彝族乡舍得村民委五家寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Shede Township 舍得彝族乡, [[Qiubei County]], [[Yunnan]] Province is unintelligible with Ku of Bainitang 白泥塘.<ref>Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. ''[https://sites.google.com/site/msealangs/sino-tibetan/ku-shidongmen Ku (Shidongmen) audio word list]''. Zenodo. {{doi|10.5281/zenodo.1123229}}</ref> *Ku of Shidongmen 石洞门,<ref name="ynszxc3">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=86779|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=广南县珠琳镇西基德村委会石洞门|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Xijide Village 西基得村, Zhulin Township 珠琳镇, [[Guangnan County]], [[Yunnan]] Province<ref>Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. ''[https://sites.google.com/site/msealangs/sino-tibetan/ku-wujiazhai Ku (Wujiazhai) audio word list]''. Zenodo. {{doi|10.5281/zenodo.1122945}}</ref>
